The paper deals with the semantics of database mappings and their algebraic properties, which are core topics in the field of databases (cs.DB). It also uses concepts from category theory, such as monads and Kleisli categories, which are relevant to logic and semantics (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of complex query computations, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
